<html>
<head>
    <title>Biryani</title>
    </head>
    <body>
    <h1>Chicken Biryani Recipe</h1>
    <img src="file:///C:/Users/TOSHIBA%20TECRA/Downloads/image.png" alt="Chicken Biryani">
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <p>Chicken</p>
    <p>Basmati rice</p>
    <p>Onions</p>
    <p>Tomatoes</p>
    <p>Yogurt</p>
    <p>Cooking oil or ghee</p>
    <p>Bay leaves</p>
    <p>Cinnamon sticks</p>
    <p>Green cardamom</p>
    <p>Cloves</p>
    <p>Red chili powder</p>
    <p>Turmeric powder</p>
    <p>Coriander powder</p>
    <p>Cumin powder</p>
    <p>Garam masala</p>
    <p>Salt</p>
    <p>Ginger garlic paste</p>
    <p>Green chilies</p>
    <p>Fresh coriander (hara dhania)</p>
    <p>Fresh mint (pudina)</p>
    <p>Lemon juice</p>
    <p>Biryani essence / kewra water (optional)</p>
    <p>Saffron (optional)</p>
    <p>Potatoes (optional)</p>
    <p>Fried onions</p>
    <h3>Method</h3>
    <p>Boil rice (70% cooked), then drain.</p>
    <p>Heat oil, fry onion until golden.</p>
    <p>Add chicken + ginger garlic paste, cook 5 mins.</p>
    <p>Add tomato, yogurt, biryani masala, and salt. Cook until chicken is done.</p>
    <p>Add half rice, then chicken, then remaining rice.</p>
    <p>Sprinkle mint/coriander, cover, and cook on low heat for 10–15 mins (dum).</p>
    <a href="https://youtu.be/R4KCSyiDLb4?si=suAkHsUwcC30kdLD">Click here for recipe</a>
    </body>
</html>
